Main concepts of  health economics and their implementation in health care management and health policy will be provided. Special features of market relations, risk and insurance in health care, also basic terms and methods of economic assessment will be considered.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide basic knowledge about main concepts and methods of research in health economics and to describe their implementation in health care management and health policy.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who successfully finish the course should know: - the structure of health economics and principal questions of different parts of subject; - the content of main terms and can use them in health care management in health policy; - and can analyse the concept of demand and supply in health care; - know basic principles of uncertainty and insurance;  - and can use in practice basic knowledge in methods of economic assessment.
